leader /ˈliːdə/

(leaders) 

1. N-COUNT The leader of a group of people or an organization is the person who is in control of it or in charge of it. 领导人 

例： We now need a new leader of the party and a new style of leadership. 我们现在需要一个新的政党领导人和一种新的领导风格。 

2. N-COUNT The leader at a particular point in a race or competition is the person who is winning at that point. 领先者 

例： The leaders came in two minutes clear of the field. 领先的选手们早两分钟到达终点。 

3. N-COUNT The leader of an orchestra is the most senior violin player, who acts as a deputy to the conductor. (交响乐团的)首席小提琴手 [英国英语] 

4. N-COUNT A leader in a newspaper is a piece of writing which gives the editor's opinion on an important news item. (报纸上的)社评 [英国英语]

